{"title_page": "Vincenzo Amendola", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Vincenzo Amendola\n| image = Vincenzo Amendola (cropped).jpg\n| office = [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]]\n| termstart = 5 September 2019\n| termend = \n| predecessor = [[Lorenzo Fontana]]\n| successor =\n| office2 = Member of the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| termstart2 = 15 March 2013\n| termend2 = 22 March 2018\n| constituency2 = [[Campania]] \n\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1973|12|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Naples]], [[Italy]]\n| party = [[Democrats of the Left|DS]] {{small|(1999\u20132007)}}<br>[[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]] {{small|(2007\u2013present)}}\n| spouse = {{marriage|Karima Moual|2013}}\n| children= 2\n}}\n\n'''Vincenzo \"Enzo\" Amendola''' (born 22 December 1973) is an Italian [[politician]], member of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]]. On 5 September 2019, Amendola was appointed [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]] in the [[Conte II Cabinet|second government]] of [[Giuseppe Conte]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.insideover.com/economia/la-troika-del-pd-vigila-sullitalia.html|title=La guardia della troika Pd sull'ortodossia europeista|date=2019-10-05|website=InsideOver|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nVincenzo Amendola was born in [[Naples]] in 1973.\n\nDuring the [[1990s]] he joined the [[Left Youth (Italy)|Left Youth]] (SG), the youth wing of the [[Democrats of the Left]] (DS), the main [[social democracy|social democratic]] party in Italy. In 1998, he was appointed SG's responsible for foreign affairs as well as vice president of the [[International Union of Socialist Youth]]\u00a0(IUSY), of which he was elected secretary general in 2001.<ref>[https://www.esteri.it/mae/it/ministero/viceministri_sottosegretari/vincenzo-amendola Segretario Vincenzo Amendola], Minister degli Esteri</ref> In 2006, he was appointed in the national secretariat of the DS, and in November 2006, he was elected regional secretary of DS for [[Campania]].\n\nTogether with the majority of DS members, in 2007 he joined the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD), the new centre-left party, born from the union between DS and the [[The Daisy]].<ref>{{Cite book |first=Bruno |last=Vespa |title=Il Cuore e la Spada: Storia politica e romantica dell'Italia unita, 1861-2011 |publisher=Mondadori |year=2010 |page=650 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YpRt-k0VDEEC&pg=PA650|isbn=9788852017285 }}</ref><ref>{{citation|first=Giuliano |last=Augusto |title=De profundis per il Pd |newspaper=Rinascita |date=8 December 2013 |url=http://www.rinascita.eu/index.php?action=news&id=22749 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301073618/http://www.rinascita.eu/index.php?action=news&id=22749 |archivedate=1 March 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref> In October 2009 he won the primary election to became regional secretary of the PD for Campania, a position that he held until 2014.<ref>[https://quifinanza.it/finanza/vincenzo-amendola-chi-e-nuovo-ministro-degli-affari-europei/306247/ Enzo Amendola: chi \u00e8 il nuovo Ministro degli Affari Europei], quifinanza.it</ref>\n\nIn the [[2013 Italian general election|2013 general election]] he was elected to the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]] for the Campania constituency.<ref>[https://elezionistorico.interno.gov.it/candidati.php?tpel=C&dtel=24/02/2013&tpa=I&tpe=I&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=20&levsut1=1&ne1=20&es0=S&es1=S&ms=S&ne=20&nlg=21&ccp=3456&ts=C Elezioni del 2013: Circoscrizione Campania 2], Ministero dell'Interno</ref> As a deputy, he was appointed in the Foreign Affairs Commission, where he was elected leader of the PD's group.<ref>[https://www.camera.it/leg17/29?tipoAttivita=attivita&idLegislatura=17&tipoVisAtt=&shadow_deputato=305931 Vincenzo Amendola], Camera dei Deputati</ref>\n\nOn 24 June 2013, Amendola married Karima Moual, an Italian journalist with [[Moroccan people|moroccan]] ancestry,<ref>[https://www.affaritaliani.it/politica/epifani-e-orlando-al-matrimonio240613.html Epifani e Orlando al matrimonio di Enzo Amendola], affaritaliani.it</ref> from whom he had two children.<ref>[https://www.corriere.it/sette/politica/19_novembre_22/ministro-vincenzo-amendola-nel-pd-tante-vittime-renzi-24da0ea8-0900-11ea-b74a-83e463a73bb9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=yatLZY4D&pids=FR&credits=1&origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Fsette%2Fpolitica%2F19_novembre_22%2Fministro-vincenzo-amendola-nel-pd-tante-vittime-renzi-24da0ea8-0900-11ea-b74a-83e463a73bb9.shtml Il ministro Vincenzo Amendola: \"Nel Pd tante vittime di Renzi\"], Corriere della Sera</ref>\n\nIn June 2013, PD's acting secretary, [[Guglielmo Epifani]], appointed Amendola in the national secretariat, as coordinator of regional secretaries.<ref>[https://formiche.net/gallerie/amendola-ministro-affari-europei/ Chi \u00e8 Vincenzo Amendola, nuovo ministro per gli Affari europei], formiche.net</ref> In December 2013, [[Matteo Renzi]] became the new party's leader and Amendola was not confirmed in the secretariat; however, after only few months, many members of Renzi's board was appointed ministers in [[Renzi Cabinet|his newly formed government]], thus Amendola was re-appointed in the secretariat as responsible for Foreign and European Affairs in September 2014. He was also responsible for relations with the [[Party of European Socialists]].<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2014/09/16/news/pd_al_via_la_direzione_per_una_segreteria_unitaria-95908371/ Renzi nomina la nuova 'segreteria unitaria' del Pd: 8 donne e 7 uomini. Minoranza dentro], ''la Repubblica''</ref>\n\nOn 29 January 2016, Amendola was appointed undersecretary to the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Italy)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] in Renzi's cabinet, a position that he held until 1 June 2018, serving under the premiership of [[Paolo Gentiloni]] too.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/it/governo-gentiloni-dal-12122016/6290 Governo Gentiloni], governo.it</ref> In both governments, he had been responsible for Italians abroad and for environmental and energy policies. During his term he often accompanied the President of the Republic, [[Sergio Mattarella]], on international state visits.\n\nThe [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]] resulted in a historic defeat for the PD and Amendola, who run for the [[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate of the Republic]], did not succeeded in being elected.<ref>[https://elezionistorico.interno.gov.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=04/03/2018&tpa=I&tpe=M&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=15&levsut1=1&lev2=3&levsut2=2&ne1=15&ne2=153&es0=S&es1=S&es2=S&ms=S Elezioni del 2018: Circoscrizione Campania 3], Ministero dell'Interno</ref>\n\nOn 15 June 2019, the new party's leader, [[Nicola Zingaretti]], appointed Amendola party's responsible for Foreign Affairs.<ref>[https://www.democratica.com/focus/membri-segreteria-zingaretti/ Ecco chi sono i membri della segreteria di Zingaretti], ''Democratica''</ref>\n\n===Minister of European Affairs===\nIn August 2019 tensions grew within the [[Conte I Cabinet|populist government]], leading to the issuing of a motion of no-confidence on Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] by the [[Lega Nord|League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|title=Italy's Government Collapses, Turning Chaos Into Crisis|first=Jason|last=Horowitz|date=20 August 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> After Conte's resignation, the national board of the PD officially opened to the possibility of forming a new cabinet in a coalition with the M5S,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|title=Italian PM resigns with attack on 'opportunist' Salvini|first=Angela|last=Giuffrida|date=20 August 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref> based on pro-Europeanism, [[green economy]], [[sustainable development]], fight against [[economic inequality]] and a new immigration policy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/08/21/news/governo_il_testo_integrale_della_relazione_di_zingaretti_alla_direzione_pd-234041294/|title=Governo, Zingaretti: \"I 5 punti per trattare con il M5S. No accordicchi, governo di svolta\"|date=21 August 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref> The party also accepted that Conte may continue at the head of a new government,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|title=Conte wins crucial support for new Italian govt coalition|website=Washington Post}}</ref> and on 29 August President [[Sergio Mattarella]] formally invested Conte to do so.<ref>{{cite web |title=Il Presidente Mattarella ha conferito l'incarico al Prof. Conte di formare il Governo |url=https://www.quirinale.it/elementi/35484 |website=Quirinale |accessdate=29 August 2019 |language=it}}</ref> On 5 September, Amendola was appointed new [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/it/governo/conte-ii/ministro/enzo-amendola Vincenzo Amendola \u2013 Ministro per gli Affari Europei], governo.it</ref>\n\n==Electoral history==\n{|class=wikitable style=\"width:55%; border:1px #AAAAFF solid\"\n|-\n! width=12%|Election\n! width=25%|House\n! width=25%|Constituency\n! width=5% colspan=\"2\"|Party\n! width=12%|Votes\n! width=12%|Result\n|-\n! [[2013 Italian general election|2013]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[Campania]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Democratic Party (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n| \u2013{{efn|name=fn1|Elected in a [[closed list]] proportional representation system.}}\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|-\n! [[2018 Italian general election|2018]]\n| [[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate of the Republic]]\n| [[Campania]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Democratic Party (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n| \u2013{{efn|name=fn1}}\n| {{nowrap|{{cross|15}} '''Not elected'''}}\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reference list}}\n{{Conte II Cabinet}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party (Italy) politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Naples]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Conte II Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Deputies of Legislature XVII of Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Vincenzo Amendola\n| image = Vincenzo Amendola (cropped).jpg\n| office = [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]]\n| termstart = 5 September 2019\n| termend = \n| predecessor = [[Lorenzo Fontana]]\n| successor =\n| office2 = Member of the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| termstart2 = 15 March 2013\n| termend2 = 22 March 2018\n| constituency2 = [[Campania]] \n\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1973|12|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Naples]], [[Italy]]\n| party = [[Democrats of the Left|DS]] {{small|(1999\u20132007)}}<br>[[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]] {{small|(2007\u2013present)}}\n| spouse = {{marriage|Karima Moual|2013}}\n| children= 2\n}}\n\n'''Vincenzo \"Enzo\" Amendola''' (born 22 December 1973) is an Italian [[politician]], member of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]]. On 5 September 2019, Amendola was appointed [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]] in the [[Conte II Cabinet|second government]] of [[Giuseppe Conte]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.insideover.com/economia/la-troika-del-pd-vigila-sullitalia.html|title=La guardia della troika Pd sull'ortodossia europeista|date=2019-10-05|website=InsideOver|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nVincenzo Amendola was born in [[Naples]] in 1973.\n\nDuring the [[1990s]] he joined the [[Left Youth (Italy)|Left Youth]] (SG), the youth wing of the [[Democrats of the Left]] (DS), the main [[social democracy|social democratic]] party in Italy. In 1998, he was appointed SG's responsible for foreign affairs as well as vice president of the [[International Union of Socialist Youth]]\u00a0(IUSY), of which he was elected secretary general in 2001.<ref>[https://www.esteri.it/mae/it/ministero/viceministri_sottosegretari/vincenzo-amendola Segretario Vincenzo Amendola], Minister degli Esteri</ref> In 2006, he was appointed in the national secretariat of the DS, and in November 2006, he was elected regional secretary of DS for [[Campania]].\n\nTogether with the majority of DS members, in 2007 he joined the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD), the new centre-left party, born from the union between DS and the [[The Daisy]].<ref>{{Cite book |first=Bruno |last=Vespa |title=Il Cuore e la Spada: Storia politica e romantica dell'Italia unita, 1861-2011 |publisher=Mondadori |year=2010 |page=650 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YpRt-k0VDEEC&pg=PA650|isbn=9788852017285 }}</ref><ref>{{citation|first=Giuliano |last=Augusto |title=De profundis per il Pd |newspaper=Rinascita |date=8 December 2013 |url=http://www.rinascita.eu/index.php?action=news&id=22749 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301073618/http://www.rinascita.eu/index.php?action=news&id=22749 |archivedate=1 March 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref> In October 2009 he won the primary election to became regional secretary of the PD for Campania, a position that he held until 2014.<ref>[https://quifinanza.it/finanza/vincenzo-amendola-chi-e-nuovo-ministro-degli-affari-europei/306247/ Enzo Amendola: chi \u00e8 il nuovo Ministro degli Affari Europei], quifinanza.it</ref>\n\nIn the [[2013 Italian general election|2013 general election]] he was elected to the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]] for the Campania constituency.<ref>[https://elezionistorico.interno.gov.it/candidati.php?tpel=C&dtel=24/02/2013&tpa=I&tpe=I&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=20&levsut1=1&ne1=20&es0=S&es1=S&ms=S&ne=20&nlg=21&ccp=3456&ts=C Elezioni del 2013: Circoscrizione Campania 2], Ministero dell'Interno</ref> As a deputy, he was appointed in the Foreign Affairs Commission, where he was elected leader of the PD's group.<ref>[https://www.camera.it/leg17/29?tipoAttivita=attivita&idLegislatura=17&tipoVisAtt=&shadow_deputato=305931 Vincenzo Amendola], Camera dei Deputati</ref>\n\nOn 24 June 2013, Amendola married Karima Moual, an Italian journalist with [[moroccan]] ancestry,<ref>[https://www.affaritaliani.it/politica/epifani-e-orlando-al-matrimonio240613.html Epifani e Orlando al matrimonio di Enzo Amendola], affaritaliani.it</ref> from whom he had two children.<ref>[https://www.corriere.it/sette/politica/19_novembre_22/ministro-vincenzo-amendola-nel-pd-tante-vittime-renzi-24da0ea8-0900-11ea-b74a-83e463a73bb9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=yatLZY4D&pids=FR&credits=1&origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Fsette%2Fpolitica%2F19_novembre_22%2Fministro-vincenzo-amendola-nel-pd-tante-vittime-renzi-24da0ea8-0900-11ea-b74a-83e463a73bb9.shtml Il ministro Vincenzo Amendola: \"Nel Pd tante vittime di Renzi\"], Corriere della Sera</ref>\n\nIn June 2013, PD's acting secretary, [[Guglielmo Epifani]], appointed Amendola in the national secretariat, as coordinator of regional secretaries.<ref>[https://formiche.net/gallerie/amendola-ministro-affari-europei/ Chi \u00e8 Vincenzo Amendola, nuovo ministro per gli Affari europei], formiche.net</ref> In December 2013, [[Matteo Renzi]] became the new party's leader and Amendola was not confirmed in the secretariat; however, after only few months, many members of Renzi's board was appointed ministers in [[Renzi Cabinet|his newly formed government]], thus Amendola was re-appointed in the secretariat as responsible for Foreign and European Affairs in September 2014. He was also responsible for relations with the [[Party of European Socialists]].<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2014/09/16/news/pd_al_via_la_direzione_per_una_segreteria_unitaria-95908371/ Renzi nomina la nuova 'segreteria unitaria' del Pd: 8 donne e 7 uomini. Minoranza dentro], ''la Repubblica''</ref>\n\nOn 29 January 2016, Amendola was appointed undersecretary to the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Italy)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] in Renzi's cabinet, a position that he held until 1 June 2018, serving under the premiership of [[Paolo Gentiloni]] too.<ref>[http://www.governo.it/it/governo-gentiloni-dal-12122016/6290 Governo Gentiloni], governo.it</ref> In both governments, he had been responsible for Italians abroad and for environmental and energy policies. During his term he often accompanied the President of the Republic, [[Sergio Mattarella]], on international state visits.\n\nThe [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]] resulted in a historic defeat for the PD and Amendola, who run for the [[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate of the Republic]], did not succeeded in being elected.<ref>[https://elezionistorico.interno.gov.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=04/03/2018&tpa=I&tpe=M&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=15&levsut1=1&lev2=3&levsut2=2&ne1=15&ne2=153&es0=S&es1=S&es2=S&ms=S Elezioni del 2018: Circoscrizione Campania 3], Ministero dell'Interno</ref>\n\nOn 15 June 2019, the new party's leader, [[Nicola Zingaretti]], appointed Amendola party's responsible for Foreign Affairs.<ref>[https://www.democratica.com/focus/membri-segreteria-zingaretti/ Ecco chi sono i membri della segreteria di Zingaretti], ''Democratica''</ref>\n\n===Minister of European Affairs===\nIn August 2019 tensions grew within the [[Conte I Cabinet|populist government]], leading to the issuing of a motion of no-confidence on Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] by the [[Lega Nord|League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|title=Italy's Government Collapses, Turning Chaos Into Crisis|first=Jason|last=Horowitz|date=20 August 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> After Conte's resignation, the national board of the PD officially opened to the possibility of forming a new cabinet in a coalition with the M5S,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|title=Italian PM resigns with attack on 'opportunist' Salvini|first=Angela|last=Giuffrida|date=20 August 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref> based on pro-Europeanism, [[green economy]], [[sustainable development]], fight against [[economic inequality]] and a new immigration policy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/08/21/news/governo_il_testo_integrale_della_relazione_di_zingaretti_alla_direzione_pd-234041294/|title=Governo, Zingaretti: \"I 5 punti per trattare con il M5S. No accordicchi, governo di svolta\"|date=21 August 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref> The party also accepted that Conte may continue at the head of a new government,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|title=Conte wins crucial support for new Italian govt coalition|website=Washington Post}}</ref> and on 29 August President [[Sergio Mattarella]] formally invested Conte to do so.<ref>{{cite web |title=Il Presidente Mattarella ha conferito l'incarico al Prof. Conte di formare il Governo |url=https://www.quirinale.it/elementi/35484 |website=Quirinale |accessdate=29 August 2019 |language=it}}</ref> On 5 September, Amendola was appointed new [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]].<ref>[http://www.governo.it/it/governo/conte-ii/ministro/enzo-amendola Vincenzo Amendola \u2013 Ministro per gli Affari Europei], governo.it</ref>\n\n==Electoral history==\n{|class=wikitable style=\"width:55%; border:1px #AAAAFF solid\"\n|-\n! width=12%|Election\n! width=25%|House\n! width=25%|Constituency\n! width=5% colspan=\"2\"|Party\n! width=12%|Votes\n! width=12%|Result\n|-\n! [[2013 Italian general election|2013]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[Campania]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Democratic Party (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n| \u2013{{efn|name=fn1|Elected in a [[closed list]] proportional representation system.}}\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|-\n! [[2018 Italian general election|2018]]\n| [[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate of the Republic]]\n| [[Campania]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Democratic Party (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Democratic Party (Italy)|PD]]\n| \u2013{{efn|name=fn1}}\n| {{nowrap|{{cross|15}} '''Not elected'''}}\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reference list}}\n{{Conte II Cabinet}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party (Italy) politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Naples]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Conte II Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Deputies of Legislature XVII of Italy]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toMoroccan(link changed toMoroccan people) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vincenzo_Amendola"}
